  "texts": [
    "Moving to layer (l + 1), attribute features for the same student are denoted as x l+1 i. N (x l i) signifies neighboring nodes in relation to x l i in layer l. Given the potential presence of redundant or irrelevant edges in the k-NN graph, this approach aids in extracting meaningful and positive correlations within the attribute-base graph.",
    "More specifically, aggregation operation (AGG) is defined for feature x i in layer l in this mannerx l+1 i = x j l ∈N (x i l) α L i, j FFN(x j l + x i l) +α H i, j FFN(x j l -x i l), (14)where α L i, j and α H i, j are learnable attention weights for the low and high filters, respectively.",
    "FNN represents a fully connected layer, succeeded by the sigmoid function.",
    "The update process is defined as:x i l+1 = U P D([x i l, AGG(•; W agg)]; W upd), with square brackets [,] representing a concatenation operation.",
    "RGCN blocks:The purpose of using RGCN blocks is to adapt to the dynamic and heterogeneous nature of the attribute-based graphs."
